    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-11-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="539"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Von
                        Baumbach.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 13, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to return with my thanks the
                    accompaniment of your letter of the 24th of September last, which has been read
                    with much interest. The just and enlightened views expressed by the Bavarian
                    government in relation to the principles under which aliens in the United States
                    are under certain circumstances held liable to military duty are very
                    satisfactory.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <p rend="right">WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">L. Von Batjmbach,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">Consul of
                        Bavaria, Milwaukee, Wisconsin</hi>.</p>
                <p>Pour copie conforme a l’original, Munich le 25 Septembre, 1867.</p>
                <p>Le Secretaire General au ministre Royal des Affaires Etrangères de Barière.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D. BERTELI.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
